document_data.History:
In {{yearlink|1357}}, Tessaril Winter instructed [[Shandril Shessair]] and [[Narm Tamaraith]] to join Voldovan's caravan to make the road from [[Scornubel]] to [[Waterdeep]], telling them also that [[Beldimarr]] and [[Arauntar]], of his men, were Harpers.{{cite book/Hand of Fire/TPB 2002|46|3}} They were aided in finding him by [[Marlel]], who cautioned them Orthil was leaving on the morning. Once they finally came across Orthil Voldovan, he wanted initially ten [[gold piece]]s for Narm and Shandril, but she talked him down to four.

He departed Scornubel with a caravan of thirty-two wagons, plus two "ready-wagons", one wagon for strongboxes and small cargo, and a cook wagon. Orthil was pleased when Shandril and Narm asked to disguise themselves as guards, which they did during the departure from Scornubel. However, even from the start, one of his guards, [[Storstil]], was slain almost as soon as they left Scornubel, and spells in the wagons killed two people. He quickly began to suspect Shandril and Narm at that point, though he had eyewitnesses that placed them away from the murder scenes.

Orthil claimed to be traveling with one mage, but believe there were a dozen more amongst the travelers; rather than find the culprit, he priorized making it to [[Face Crag]] before nightfall, which made for a better defensible position.{{cite book/Hand of Fire/TPB 2002|87-89|6}} Along the way, they were attacked before making it to the crag.{{cite book/Hand of Fire/TPB 2002|95-100|6}}

During the ambush, Voldovan tied up Narm, believing him to have gone out of line by trying to go find Shandril, abandoning his post, rather than protecting the part of the caravan where he had been assigned.{{cite book/Hand of Fire/TPB 2002|101-103|7}} Voldovan later approached Shandril, who was with Thorst; he called on her to find some of his healing accoutrements, and ordered Arauntar and Beldimarr, one of which had slain two bandits during the ambush, to drive Thorst's wagon.{{cite book/Hand of Fire/TPB 2002|105-109|7}}

Arauntar informed Shandril one morning during the run that she was oversleeping and Orthil was in a rush. Orthil later personally came to demand why she wasn't up. Over some [[thrusk]], Orthil informed them that a number of people had gone missing during the night, and that there were tracks of wild beasts near the caravan, but none of them came to the caravan itself, and also that bandits would almost certainly be shadowing the caravan along the path still. During their conversation Arauntar and Beldimarr turned up and said how they'd arranged for some goods to be moved to the abandoned wagons, still in better shape; Shandril resolved she and Narm would drive on the same wagon, which Beldimarr approved of, claiming they'd be easier to keep track of. Orthil accepted that arrangement.{{cite book/Hand of Fire/TPB 2002|135-143|9}}

During that morning, Arauntar and Beldimarr inspected the wagon belonging to [[Mhegras]] and [[Sabran]], twice; the second time, they checked on the secret floor they had spotted the first time. Voldovan was summoned for that. {{cite book/Hand of Fire/TPB 2002|145-148|9}} The master of the caravan brought along Shandril and Narm, and the latter checked the contraband horse barding for magic; finding nothing of interest, they left.{{cite book/Hand of Fire/TPB 2002|155-157|10}}

After a later ambush, Orthil Voldovan personally sought out Shandril and Narm, and took them to Arauntar and Beldimarr. The latter was about to fulfill a pact with Arauntar, to dispatch him painlessly if mortally wounded; instead, Shandril used her spellfire to heal him.{{cite book/Hand of Fire/TPB 2002|165-167|10}} She later used her power to heal Beldimarr; she found the limit of her strength there. Voldovan called afterwards on everyone to hurry to [[Orcskull Rise]].{{cite book/Hand of Fire/TPB 2002|169-175|11}}

During the next ambush, after Orcskull Rise, Shandril heard Orthil's expletives to the spell that [[Aumlar Chauntoun]] called down, which was rather crude.{{cite book/Hand of Fire/TPB 2002|221|13}} Orthil Voldovan started considering swording Shandril more seriously after he noticed about a dozen wagons wrecked and on fire at the end of the ambush.{{cite book/Hand of Fire/TPB 2002|255|15}} Approaching Triel, Voldovan told Darhabran Windhome that he was already willing to kill Shandril.{{cite book/Hand of Fire/TPB 2002|278-284|16}}

At Duskview house, Orthil Voldovan and Beldimarr met with herald Stormshield for hiring new sellswords as guards.{{cite book/Hand of Fire/TPB 2002|285-287|17}} Briefly, Beldimarr was distracted by another Harper he'd never seen telling him the Three Laws would soon apply on every city; Orthil, after that moment, seemed to have difficulty recognizing Beldimarr, and spoke more stiffly.{{cite book/Hand of Fire/TPB 2002|300-302|17}}
